# ========================
# Pre-push bypass audit log (T-063)
# ========================
# Both pre-push hooks append a JSONL line here when CF_SKIP_REVIEW=1 is
# honored. Local accumulation only — quarterly retros read it on disk and
# never sync to repo. See `.harness/README.md`.
.harness/skip-review.log

# ========================
# Mutation testing (T-060)
# ========================
# `mutmut run` writes a sandbox copy of the codebase + per-mutant metadata
# into `api/mutants/`. The sandbox is fully reproducible from
# `[tool.mutmut]` in `api/pyproject.toml`; checking it in just bloats
# the repo. The committed `.harness/mutation-baseline.json` is the only
# artifact the workflow needs to keep across runs.
api/mutants/
api/drift-report.txt
.coverage
api/.coverage
api/coverage.xml

# .claude/: ignore everything by default, but track the project-shared
# settings, agents, and hooks (per-user state like settings.local.json
# and scheduled_tasks.lock stay out).
.claude/*
!.claude/settings.json
!.claude/agents
!.claude/agents/**
!.claude/hooks
!.claude/hooks/**
